Mannatech Reviews
¬†Mannatech Inc 







                                    is the leading developer, researcher, and 







                                    marketer of glyconutrients in the form of 







                                    Mannatech Vitamins and products.¬† 







                                    Mannatech Inc was founded in the early 90's 







                                    and is based out of Coppell, TX.¬† The 







                                    company is publicly traded on the NASDAQ and 







                                    is considered to be a mid-cap Corp.¬†







                                    
Mannatech Inc now operates in a variety 







                                    of countries around the globe including the 







                                    United States, Germany, Japan, Canada, and 







                                    the UK.¬† Mannatech products include 







                                    vitamins and supplements headed by the 







                                    flagship product Ambrotose.¬† 
The full Mannatech Inc product line 







                                    includes 25 nutritional supplements, 3 







                                    topical creams, and 4 weight loss inducing 







                                    products.¬† These are all sold through a 







                                    Multi level Marketing system.¬† 
Although Mannatech Inc does 







                                    extensive research on all its products and 







                                    the board is headed by several renowned 







                                    scientists there is controversy over the 







                                    validity of their research trials.¬† 







                                    They have not conducted controlled clinical 







                                    trials for all their products, meaning that 







                                    they have not been tested against a placebo.¬† 







                                    The only one that they did perform revealed 







                                    no significant benefit of glyconutrients and 







                                    their derivative products. 
However many people testify to the 







                                    healing powers of Ambrotose, claiming that 







                                    it's responsible for treating everything 







                                    from eczema to lupus.¬† Again the 







                                    validity of these claims has not been 







                                    verified.¬† Despite the controversy 







                                    Mannatech Inc does have some very noble 







                                    goals and programs.¬† Including a 







                                    program designed to help ailing children 







                                    with nutritional deficiencies strengthen 







                                    their immune systems.
On top of the questionable effectiveness 







                                    of Mannatech products there are a 







                                    couple more warning signs.¬† Two of the 







                                    founders have questionable pasts and 







                                    Mannatech Inc is currently under 







                                    investigation by the Texas Attorney General 







                                    for alleged violation of the Deceptive Trade 







                                    Practices Act.¬† 
Find out as much 







                                    information as you can from the rep 







                                    recruiting you into this business and ask 







                                    for some valid proof of earnings as well.
If you're at Reviewopedia.com because you're looking for a way to make money online then check out our article  "7 Ways to Make Money Online" - methods that anyone can use to earn an income from home. 
